  "prompt": "What universities does Lakeland Financial recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Lakeland Financial Corporation, headquartered in Warsaw, Indiana, typically recruits new graduates from a range of universities, particularly those in the Midwest region. While the company does not publicly disclose a specific list of universities, it is known to partner with institutions such as:\n\n1. **Indiana University (IU)**  \n2. **Purdue University**  \n3. **Ball State University**  \n4. **Butler University**  \n5. **University of Notre Dame**  \n6. **Indiana Wesleyan University**  \n7. **Manchester University**  \n8. **Valparaiso University**\n\nThese partnerships are often part of their campus recruitment programs or through career fairs.\n\n### Majors They Look For\nLakeland Financial recruits graduates with a variety of majors, depending on the role. Common majors include:\n\n1. **Finance**  \n2. **Accounting**  \n3. **Business Administration**  \n4. **Economics**  \n5. **Marketing**  \n6. **Information Systems or Technology** (for technology-related roles)  \n7. **Management**  \n8. **Communications** (for customer service or marketing roles)\n\nThe company values candidates with strong analytical skills, communication abilities, and a passion for the banking and financial services industry. Networking, internships, and involvement in relevant extracurricular activities can also enhance a candidate\u2019s prospects.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it\u2019s best to check Lakeland Financial\u2019s **careers page** or contact their HR department directly.",
